CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 24, 1946 reads: "Pretty Wedding - Mr. and Mrs. Walter James Whaley were married in Sewickley Aug. 15, at St. Matthew AME Zion Church. in wedding party were Mrs. Laura Brannon, matron of honor; bridesmaids, Mrs. Dorothy Cottom and Miss Carolyn Farrington.  Ring bearer was Elmer Steele Jr., best man was Walter J. Brannon, and ushers, Charles Cottom and Ralph Lee. Mrs. Whaley is the former Ruth Tice McDonald. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Bride Ruth McDonald Whaley and groom Walter James Whaley walking out of St. Matthews AME Zion Church, Sewickley
